column5: EYEG i view the news as a update but not a material event If you read their PRs they always have a super positive spin Eyegate gets positive nasdaq listing determination or FDA approves clinical trial that same product was previously approved for human testing Reality example get Nasdaq compliance done by september or else
EYEG Good rule of thumb is if theres tangible good news you can buy The news here was a non event aka pump Now they dumping
EYEG Goin under 20 like I said If youre an investor I suggest a 6 month hold for top line data Otherwise you are just getting pumpoozled
